content.description: Start matching in rail down in the hole on the left side of the overhanging face.  Use feet out right.  Go up on good holds to arete/lip.  Go to the top using the left arete.  Do some wizard $hit and high steps while using the slopey hand holds on the arête to make a desperate move to the top.  Very rewarding. A low start on the footholds of the normal prob adds a grade to the problem and a couple fun moves.
content.protection: As many pads and spotters as you can bring unless you have cajones to do it solo.
content.location: On the right side of the trail up the slope in the talus field.  Just before the 420 boulder and on the opposite side of the Gavel boulder.  One of the first boulders you see.

content.description:
Same boulder as

Wise Mans Fear

.  Start mid-way on V-hold on right side of the Wise Mans Fear boulder.  Make shoulder moves out left up rail and topout like in as

Wise Mans Fear

.   Super powerful and scary!
content.protection: Lots of pads and friends that do not give California spots.
